Cooked karambwan are a type of food that can be obtained by thoroughly cooking raw karambwan on a fire or cooking range, requiring level 30 Cooking and granting 190 experience when successful. Players may burn a karambwan while cooking one, resulting in a burnt karambwan; the burn rate while cooking these will decrease as players reach higher Cooking levels. It will stop burning entirely at Cooking level 99 on both ranges and fires.

In order to thoroughly cook raw karambwan, a player must first complete Tai Bwo Wannai Trio and then talk to Tinsay afterwards.[1][2] Otherwise, players can only cook it into poison karambwan.

Eating cooked karambwan heals 18 Hitpoints when eaten. Unlike most other food, they can be consumed nearly instantly with no delay after consuming another food item, such as a shark, known as "combo eating"; this makes them a favourable item for player killing. The "combo eating" tactic can be enhanced further by drinking a dose of Saradomin brew alongside a karambwan and the base food item, enabling a player to heal over 50 Hitpoints very rapidly. An additional benefit is that eating a karambwan in combat only adds a delay of two ticks before the player can attack again, while most other foods have a delay of three ticks.

It is possible to use tick manipulation to cook raw karambwans in one tick (where other food takes four) to obtain a large amount of Cooking experience in a shorter amount of time.

The "combo eating" tactic can be enhanced further by drinking a dose of [[Saradomin brew]] alongside a karambwan and the base food item, enabling a player to heal over 50 Hitpoints very rapidly. An additional benefit is that eating a karambwan in combat only adds a delay of two ticks before the player can attack again, while most other foods have a delay of three ticks.
